  "issue_title": "feature: define OCR fallback boundary for weak screens",
  "issue_body": "Parent: #38\n\n## Problem\n\nSome Android screens expose weak or incomplete Accessibility data. TouchPilot needs a planned fallback boundary for OCR, without making OCR or local VLM required for Milestone 3 completion.\n\nThe project should know when Accessibility context is weak and how future OCR/VLM fallback will plug in.\n\n## Proposed behavior\n\nAdd weak-tree detection and define the OCR fallback boundary:\n\n```text\nAccessibility observation\n  -> screen context builder\n  -> context quality check\n  -> strong context: summarize/suggest directly\n  -> weak context: mark OCR fallback needed\n```\n\nMilestone 3 can implement the interface/detection first. OCR execution can be added when the local OCR runtime is selected.\n\n## User workflow\n\nWhen TouchPilot cannot understand enough from Accessibility data, it should respond honestly:\n\n```text\nI can see this screen, but the app exposes limited readable UI data. OCR support is needed for better understanding here.\n```\n\n## Local-first impact\n\nThis keeps the primary path local and deterministic while preparing for future local OCR/VLM support.\n\n## Safety and security considerations\n\n- OCR output should be treated as untrusted and noisy.\n- OCR text may include sensitive content and must go through redaction before logging.\n- Weak context should not cause unsafe guessing or blind tapping.\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n\n- [ ] Add context quality or weak-tree detection logic.\n- [ ] Define an OCR fallback interface/boundary or placeholder result type.\n- [ ] Mark local VLM as future fallback, not a Milestone 3 dependency.\n- [ ] Weak context produces conservative summary/suggestion behavior.\n- [ ] Tests cover strong context, weak context, and empty context.\n- [ ] Documentation or comments explain that OCR/VLM fallback remains local-only.\n\n## References\n\n- Parent issue: #38\n- `docs/LOCAL_INFERENCE.md`\n- `docs/ARCHITECTURE.md`\n",
